Package: brGDGTNPP
Type: Package
Title: Predict NPP from brGDGT data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Marco A.", "Vidal-Cordasco", 
           email = "mav54@cam.ac.uk",  
           role = c("aut", "cre")),            
    person("Andrea", "Manica", 
           email = "am315@cam.ac.uk", 
           role = "aut")
  )
Description: A tool to predict Net Primary Productivity (NPP) from relative abundance (%) of
    individual brGDGTs using centered log-ratio (CLR) transformation and a pre-trained 
    random forest model. Includes diagnostic tools to assess whether new 
    samples fall within the brGDGT composition space of the training data, 
    identifying potentially unreliable predictions. When mean annual 
    temperature and precipitation are available, the package also computes 
    potential NPP using the Miami model, allowing comparison 
    between climate-based and brGDGT-based NPP estimates to identify 
    deviations from climatic expectations.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
